comment.body:
@ulrichard: I know what you mean I'm not happy with the current state. But if I look at fireos, sallyfish, ubuntu touch and so on I see similar ideas but no cooperation. Like in so many open source areas, people should work together. 
I would love to shift phones more in a Pc direction so you can install the OS you want on them. But when I see that drivers for most of the components are closed of by the manufacturer we have a long way to go.
My solution at the moment is to run Cyanogenmod with only the essential google services and using f-Droit whenever possible.
